TOO many 4x4s were being stolen from South Africa.The thugs were driving them across the border...But the South African soldiers came up with a big plan to stop the thugs. They decided to place big rocks on the border to prevent stolen 4x4s from being driven out of the country.The Defence and Military Veterans Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula said this during a question and answer session in the National Council of Provinces on today.Members of the South African National Defence Force (SANDF) are currently protecting the borders with mobile and foot patrols.They are assisted by the South African Police Services (SAPS) and officials from the Department of Home Affairs.According to Mapisa-Nqakula South Africa&rsquo;s borders have unique challenges, referring to the 96km border between Mozambique and KwaZulu-Natal.Mapisa-Nqakula says the defence force had to come up with ways to stop criminals from crossing the border into Mozambique with 4x4 vehicles stolen in South Africa.She mentioned that the army had to place big rocks on the border to prevent criminals from driving the stolen vehicles across the border.The SANDF is currently considering using cameras and sensors in addition to the fences along the borders.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/rocks-used-to-prevent-stolen-4x4s-from-crossing-border-minister-20170510